-- BM&FBovespa Plans to Cut Brokerages' Costs by Half, Brasil Economico Says
-- Telma Marotto
-- 2010-08-02T12:16:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/bm-fbovespa-plans-to-cut-brokerages-costs-by-half-brasil-economico-says.html

          
          
             Brazil’s  BM&FBovespa SA  plans to cut
by half the monthly fixed costs brokerages pay to the exchange,
 Brasil Economico  newspaper reported, citing  Carlos Eduardo Lofrano , a director at the country’s brokerage association.  
 The bourse will announce in coming days a reduction of 30
percent on average starting this month, Lofrano told the Sao
Paulo-based newspaper. The cut will reach 50 percent by 2011,
according to the newspaper.  
